{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/thoughts/quit-social-networks/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Labidi Aymen"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"ac76ccbc-4676-52fa-9d26-a2afd0ae05bc","excerpt":"The social network is a wealth for those who know how to exploit it. I used to collect information and follow the news about technologies. I had fun sharing…","html":"<p>The social network is a wealth for those who know how to exploit it. I used to collect information and follow the news about technologies. I had fun sharing some of them. But lastly, what did I get?</p>\n<p>Certainly, a mind full of information but a mind that can’t focus on one thing.</p>\n<p>After a short time reflecting upon these facts, I decided to undertake these steps:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Get off from all social networks for a long while.</li>\n<li>Get off from the internet for a while.</li>\n<li>Look around you, look at what you miss in real life.</li>\n<li>Clean up the mess in your mind.</li>\n<li>Focus on one thing, only one thing.</li>\n<li>Share your experience.</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Few days later, things have already started to change for the better.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Give it a try!</strong></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Quit social networks","date":"August 05, 2015","description":null,"categories":["thoughts"],"cover":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/42425dd7e33edade3547e4183aeea1ac/e008e/social-networking.jpg","srcSet":"/static/42425dd7e33edade3547e4183aeea1ac/20979/social-networking.jpg 100w,\n/static/42425dd7e33edade3547e4183aeea1ac/9aa69/social-networking.jpg 200w,\n/static/42425dd7e33edade3547e4183aeea1ac/e008e/social-networking.jpg 400w","sizes":"(min-width: 400px) 400px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/42425dd7e33edade3547e4183aeea1ac/c3e0e/social-networking.avif 100w,\n/static/42425dd7e33edade3547e4183aeea1ac/c61ac/social-networking.avif 200w,\n/static/42425dd7e33edade3547e4183aeea1ac/9870f/social-networking.avif 400w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"(min-width: 400px) 400px, 100vw"},{"srcSet":"/static/42425dd7e33edade3547e4183aeea1ac/a1373/social-networking.webp 100w,\n/static/42425dd7e33edade3547e4183aeea1ac/ac5e7/social-networking.webp 200w,\n/static/42425dd7e33edade3547e4183aeea1ac/a4d68/social-networking.webp 400w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 400px) 400px, 100vw"}]},"width":400,"height":309}}}}},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/_jsy/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"_jsy"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/docteury/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Docteury"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"ac76ccbc-4676-52fa-9d26-a2afd0ae05bc","previousPostId":"a42615e2-48b2-5ce5-ac20-e03875d001cf","nextPostId":"2c625587-795a-5f58-9064-58ffd9d45c94","category":"thoughts"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2841359383"]}